               <p>416. 
               <persName id="t17430907-42-defend407" type="defendantName">
                  John 
                  Brown 
               <interp inst="t17430907-42-defend407" type="surname" value="Brown"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-42-defend407" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-42-defend407" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , of <placeName id="t17430907-42-defloc215">St Helens</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17430907-42-defloc215" type="placeName" value="St Helens"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17430907-42-defloc215" type="type" value="defendantHome"></interp>
                  <join result="persNamePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17430907-42-defend407 t17430907-42-defloc215"></join>, was indicted for <rs id="t17430907-42-off216" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17430907-42-off216" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-42-off216" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing a Handkerchief, value 18 d.
            </rs> the Goods of 
               <persName id="t17430907-42-victim408" type="victimName">
                  Josias 
                  Taylor 
               <interp inst="t17430907-42-victim408" type="surname" value="Taylor"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-42-victim408" type="given" value="Josias"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-42-victim408" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17430907-42-off216 t17430907-42-victim408"></join>
                  </persName>
            , <rs id="t17430907-42-cd217" type="crimeDate">Sept 3</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17430907-42-off216 t17430907-42-cd217"></join>.</p>
               <p>Josias Taylor. Last Saturday Evening, about eight o'Clock, I was going with a Friend to drink a Tankard of Beer, and just by my own Door, in Bishopsgate street, I found something lightly touch my Pocket; I put my Hand into my Pocket, and found that my Handkerchief was gone; I saw the Prisoner about the same Distance from me that he is now; I immediately run after him, and seized him, and said, Sirrah, you have got my Handkerchief; he took the Handkerchief out of his Pocket and threw it down directly; I took up the Handkerchief, and carried the Prisoner into a back Room; said I, Sirrah, this Practice will bring you to the Gallows; he begged that I would let him go, and said, his Father and Mother would beat him; there was a Gentleman came and said, he had picked his Pocket within these five Minutes, but he would not prosecute him; says one who had been a Constable, this is the third or fourth Time that he has been sent to Newgate: I searched his Pockets, and found these five Handkerchiefs about him. The People very well knew him.</p>

               <p>Q. to the Prisoner. How old are you?</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I am Eleven Years old. <rs id="t17430907-42-verdict218" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17430907-42-verdict218" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-42-verdict218" type="verdictSubcategory" value="theftunder1s"></interp>
               Guilty 10 d.
            </rs>
               </p>
